  "result": "The fix is complete. Here's a summary:\n\n## Summary\n\n**Root cause**: In `parseSourcesToFileScheme()` (`TemplateManager.kt:350`), when processing `<img>`, `<video>`, `<audio>`, and `<source>` tags to convert their `src` attributes to `file:///` URLs, the code uses `java.net.URI` to parse the attribute value. When a filename contains `#` (e.g., `image#1.jpg`), `URI` treats `#` as a fragment separator, so `attrUri.path` returns only `image` (the part before `#`), and the fragment `1.jpg` is lost. This results in an incorrect file path, and the image can't be found.\n\n**Fix**: In the `replaceWithFileScheme` inner function within `parseSourcesToFileScheme`, after parsing the URI, reconstruct the full filename by appending the fragment (if present) back to the path with a `#` separator. This handles Anki's legacy behavior of storing filenames with unencoded `#` in HTML.\n\n**Change**: Single file modified \u2014 `AnkiDroid/src/main/java/com/ichi2/libanki/TemplateManager.kt` (lines 367-374 added).\n\nThe downstream `getFileUri()` function already correctly encodes `#` as `%23` in the `file:///` URL because it uses the three-argument `URI(\"file\", ssp, null)` constructor which percent-encodes special characters in the scheme-specific part.",
